1. *Sviđam* se ovom novom restoranu. (I like this new restaurant.) 
2. Ona mi se *sviđa*. (I like her.)
3. Da li se tebi *sviđa* ova pesma? (Do you like this song?)
4. Ne znam zašto mi se ova haljina ne *sviđa*. (I don't know why I don't like this dress.)
5. *Sviđaš* mi se. (I like you.)
6. Jako se *sviđam* novom profesoru. (I really like the new teacher.)
7. Njima se *sviđa* ideja da putuju po Aziji. (They like the idea of traveling around Asia.)
8. Molim te, reci mi da li se *sviđa* ova boja za zidove. (Please tell me if you like this color for the walls.)
9. Oni se ne *sviđaju* meni. (I don't like them.)
10. Kako se *sviđaš* u novoj majici! (You look great in your new shirt!)

Note: The word "sviđam" is a form of the verb "sviđati se" which means "to like" in English. The word is conjugated in different forms depending on the subject and the tense of the sentence. The star (*) is used to highlight the word "sviđam" in each sentence.